<HEADLINE>
TAIWAN INVENTORS ATTEND INVENTION SHOW IN PITTSBURGH
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
New York,  June 8 (CNA) 06/09/07  16:05:53 (By Lillian Lin and
Elizabeth Hsu)
</P>
<P>
A Taiwanese delegation of inventors from enterprises,  colleges,
universities and research institutes is showcasing dozens of
inventions at the 23rd Invention and New Product Exposition
(INPEX) taking place in Pittsburgh, Pennsylvania June 6-9.
</P>
<P>
The group has set up 19 stalls at the venue, displaying
innovative products and designs ranging from body-shaping
underwear to tandem bikes made from recycled materials. It is the
largest Taiwanese group ever to have taken part in the annual
show, Chen Chung-tai,  chairman of the Taiwan Inventors
Association, said Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The Pittsburgh INPEX, one of the largest shows of its kind in the
U.S., is being attended by inventors from 20 countries, who have
brought more than 900 innovations, new product ideas and
technologies to the event.
</P>
